column2: If a country *has a medium or low electricity consumption per capita (<4200kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).

If a country *has a high electricity consumption per capita (>4200kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
What is the ratio of countries *having a high electricity consumption per capita (>4200kWh)*? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).

If a country *has a medium or high number of Internet users (>1,168,000)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
If a country *has a low number of Internet users (<1,168,000)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
What is the ratio of countries *having a low number of Internet users (<1,168,000)*? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
